page.title: 07NAGS HEAD
page.content: The{Nag's Head Public House}is situated in the{main street}of{Hulland {Ward.}The people have lived in the Public House for{five years.}The building itself is{eighty-five years {old,}but it was knocked down and {rebuilt}again in{1900.}They work at bar selling beer, crisps, peanuts, cigarettes and other things. They employ{five people}who help at the bar and collect up the empty glasses. The Public House is opened at the bar and collect up the empty glasses.The Public House is opened at{6:00pm}and closes at about{11:00pm.}Trucks are used to transport the drinks to them and the most{popular}drink is Pedigree. The bottles are{recycled}and used again.{Snack meals}are served at certain times.
